WEBVTT

00:02:28.471 --> 00:02:31.013
they finally think
you're ready for a TED Talk.

00:02:31.037 --> 00:02:32.818
(Laughter)

00:02:32.842 --> 00:02:37.414
(Applause)

00:02:37.438 --> 00:02:39.236
NL: I love being here.

00:02:39.260 --> 00:02:41.975
And I love you for agreeing to do this.

00:02:41.999 --> 00:02:43.988
EH: Thank you for asking. It's my honor.

00:02:44.012 --> 00:02:45.559
So here's my first question.

00:02:45.919 --> 00:02:47.633
Was your mother proud of you?

00:02:47.657 --> 00:02:49.653
(Laughter)

00:02:50.055 --> 00:02:51.388
NL: My mother ...

00:02:51.412 --> 00:02:52.579
what a place to start.

00:02:54.967 --> 00:02:57.118
Let me put it this way --

00:02:57.142 --> 00:02:58.762
when I came back from the war,

00:02:58.786 --> 00:03:04.374
she showed me the letters
that I had written her from overseas,